Nutritional Deficit: A Comprehensive Global Investigation

29/04/2023

The world map displays the prevalence of malnutrition among the population in different countries, represented as a percentage. The gradient bar illustrates the level of malnutrition reported in each country, with nations in Asia and Africa, including India, Sudan, and Chad, exhibiting higher levels of malnutrition compared to those in Europe and America. The bar chart provides a visual representation of the mean population across different continents between the years 2000 and 2021. The data reveals that Asia has the most substantial population compared to other continents, and is higher than the population of Europe, North America, and Oceania combined. The scatter plot displays the distribution of malnutrition data across different continents. The plot indicates that the malnutrition data in Asia is more scattered than in other continents, suggesting that the prevalence of malnutrition is not uniform throughout the continent. In contrast, continents such as Europe, Oceania, and South America have more consistent and relatively lower rates of malnutrition.
